This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method to improve the robustness of neural networks against adversarial attacks through self-supervised learning and adversarial training. It also involves classification tasks, which are commonly studied in the field of machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the proposed method is evaluated on image classification tasks, which are a common application of computer vision. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves improving the performance of neural networks through learning robust feature representations. 

cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with adversarial attacks on neural networks and proposes a defense mechanism against them. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves training neural networks and improving their robustness through self-supervised learning and adversarial training.
